				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Sulfidic tailings are high-volume wastes with a high content of sulfide minerals. They can lead to severe environmental damage if not properly managed. These tailings can undergo weathering if put in contact with oxygen and water, generating acid mine drainage (AMD). The moderate-to-high sulfide content is also an important technical limitation for their implementation. Sulfidic copper tailings with excessive sulfur content are prone to oxidation, leading to the generation of sulfates and causing compatibility issues with cement.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">硫化尾矿是硫化矿物含量较高的大量废物。如果管理不当，会对环境造成严重破坏。这些尾矿如果与氧气和水接触，就会发生风化，产生酸性矿井排水（AMD）。中高含量的硫化物也是实施这类尾矿的一个重要技术限制。硫含量过高的硫化铜尾矿容易氧化，产生硫酸盐，并导致与水泥的相容性问题。</common:generalComment>
